    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="la" resp="#MB">
                <ab>
                     <lb n="1"/>Χαρίτω<supplied reason="lost">ν</supplied>
                 <lb n="2"/>χρηστὸς
                    <lb n="3"/>καὶ ἄμενπτ<unclear>ο</unclear>
                    <lb n="4" break="no"/>ς ἒζησε
                    <lb n="5"/>ν ἔτη <num value="60">ἑξήκο
                    <lb n="6" break="no"/><supplied reason="omitted">ν</supplied>τα</num> καὶ μῆνες
                    <lb n="7"/><num value="3">γ</num> ἁμέ
                    <lb n="8" break="no"/>ρες <num value="1">α</num>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text based upon photograph and rapid autopsy</note></app>
                    <app loc="7-8"><note>Manganaro 1962 resolved the last two lines as γαμέτρας</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#MB">
                <p>Chariton, lodevole e irreprensibile, visse sessant'anni, 3 mesi, 1 giorno</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#MB">
                <p>Chariton, commendable and irreproachable, lived sixty years, 3 months, 1 day</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>In 1962, Manganaro suggested that the decoration on the side represented the tools of an agrimensor, in support of an attempt to interpret lines 7-8 as a doric form of geometres, viz gametras. As Manganaro 2001 observed, in fact this was an erroneous reading, induced by the very irregular layout of the text.</p>
            </div>
